# VMS template registry

Template file: `server/assets/template.docx` (tracked in git). Tags use docxtemplater syntax.

Execution plan: `docs/VMS-FULL-COVERAGE-PLAN.md`. Tag inventory: `docs/VMS-FIELD-MANIFEST.md` (authoritative once created). Mapped tags today: `docs/VMS-TEMPLATE-REGISTRY.md`.

When adding a VMS field, update **all** that apply:

1. Contract Word template tags (e.g. `{candidate_first_name}`, `{#professional_experiences}...`)
2. `docs/VMS-FIELD-MANIFEST.md` — tag → DB path → parse → wizard step → required at submit
3. `mapCandidateToTemplateData()` in `server/utils/docxBuilder.ts`
4. `resumeJsonSchema()` + prompts in `server/utils/geminiShared.ts` (Phase C parse)
5. `types/parse.ts` → `parse.post.ts` persistence → `applyParseResult()` in `useCandidateForm.ts`
6. Intake UI + `candidates` schema/migration + `server/utils/schemas.ts` (Phase B)
7. `server/utils/normalizeCandidate.ts` on read/write boundaries (after #11)

Unmapped template tags render blank — document known gaps in PR description until wired.

Do not use old `{first_name}` / `{#employers}` names. After contract template edits, run `node scripts/inventory-template-tags.mjs` and reconcile with manifest.
